// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 3/Product Info Sheet 1.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Info Sheet: Fusion Standard LibraryExecutive Summaryfusion-std is the core foundation for all applications running on the Supernova Runtime. It provides a familiar, standard-library-like experience (similar to Rust's std) but architected specifically for heterogeneous, distributed, and async-first environments. It abstracts the raw HyperRing operations into safe, ergonomic abstractions.Crucially, it is a Hybrid 50/50 Crypto Library by default. All secure channels established via fusion-std automatically utilise a combiner of Classical (ECC) and Post-Quantum (Lattice) algorithms, ensuring "Harvest Now, Decrypt Later" resistance without developer configuration.Product IdentityName: Fusion Standard LibraryCrate: fusion-stdRole: The Developer Experience Layer (SDK).Philosophy: "Safe abstractions for dangerous hardware. Quantum resistance by default."Key CapabilitiesRuntime Macros: #[fusion::main] automatically bootstraps the correct runtime (v1/v2/v3) based on the Fusion.toml target.Async primitives: Drop-in replacements for std::fs and std::net that use io_uring under the hood without blocking the reactor.Hybrid 50/50 Security: fusion::crypto::Identity generates keys that are valid in both pre-quantum and post-quantum regimes.Compute Traits: Uniform API for launching kernels on CPU, GPU, and QPU.Distributed Channels: Channels that work across network boundaries transparently.Target AudienceApplication Developers: Writing business logic, microservices, or AI pipelines.Security Engineers: Requiring audit-proof PQC implementation.
